      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Office of Chief Inspector of Stock. ¶ custom house, ¶ Melbourne, ¶  ¶ June 15th ¶  ¶ 18 ¶ 95 ¶ Baron Von Mueller ¶ Govt Botanist...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">95.06.15a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Pentland</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by M: 'Rec. &amp; answ 17/6/95 FvM'; M's letter not found. Letterhead includes a decorative crest of the Department of Agriculture Victoria with its motto, 'Industriae nihil impossibile' [With industry nothing is impossible].<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>MS accompanied by a Phytologic Museum of Melbourne specimen label filled out by M: 'Didiscus pilosus, Bentham'.</p>
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M had been asked about this plant<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in 1882<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by the then<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Chief Secretary,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>James Grant. His reply<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(M to J Grant, 2 May 1882) was published in a number of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>newspapers (see list under B82.05.11),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Australian veterinary journal</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(B82.06.02).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>A similar request was made by the Chief Inspector of Stock in 1887, see M to E. Curr, December 1887<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 87-12-00j), and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with M's reply<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>also<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>reported in the press.</p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">Office of Chief Inspector of Stock.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; font-variant: small-caps; ">custom house,</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; font-style: italic; ">Melbourne,</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>June 15th<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">18</seg>95</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Govt Botanist</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>I beg to forward herewith a sample of a plant known as the "<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Wild parsnip</hi>
               </seg>" with a view to your being so good as to furnish me with your professional opinion as to its properties and what effect it would have on cattle if partaken of freely. —</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your obedient Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>G. Pentland</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Chief Inspr of Stock</p>
         </div>
